h3. Summary
Group names having "&" special character once added to the Application access displays an irreversible error modal window. This is caused because JIRA is not encoding the special character to %26 and instead it's using the "&" character directly in the URL causing a 404 error on the request.

 !Screen Shot 2016-01-20 at 6.56.22 PM.png!

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Create a group name called "Test&Test" and add one user to it;
# Go to the Application access page and add this group to any of the applications;

 !Screen Shot 2016-01-20 at 6.53.47 PM.png|thumbnail! 

h3. Expected Results
To have the group added without an irreversible error modal window displayed;

h3. Actual Results
An irreversible error modal window is displaying not allowing to do anything on the Application access page anymore.

 !Screen Shot 2016-01-20 at 6.55.11 PM.png|thumbnail! 

h3.Workaround

To remove the affected group from the Application access directly on the database by following the procedure below:

# Stop JIRA;
# Identify the offending group ID by running the query below:
{code:SQL}
select id from licenserolesgroup where group_id like '%&%';
{code}
# Delete the offending group ID from Application access by running the query below:
{code:SQL}
delete from licenserolesgroup where id = <offending_id>;
{code}
# Start JIRA

